06:39.640 --> 06:44.920
Perhaps her best-received novel today is the Doppelganger Gambit, a futuristic police procedure mystery novel.

06:45.480 --> 06:50.520
A good deal of the book's appeal lies in its skillful depiction of the interaction between police officers.

06:51.100 --> 06:53.800
We asked Kelo if she got this from first-hand experience.

06:55.340 --> 06:57.860
I haven't had any practical experience in it.

06:57.860 --> 07:03.060
I did have a police officer come up to me at the Science Fiction Convention once when I'd been reading a chapter of Doppelganger.

07:03.520 --> 07:05.400
And he asked me when I worked in law enforcement.

07:07.300 --> 07:15.260
Once I decided I wanted to write a mystery science fiction, I went ahead and did more research.

07:16.020 --> 07:24.120
And I've kept into it, and of course that book itself and others have brought me into contact with more police officers.

07:24.120 --> 07:28.080
And they've passed on a lot of material to me.

07:28.940 --> 07:36.680
And so, sort of actually working in it myself, like I have gotten very familiar with it.

07:37.020 --> 07:45.080
And I suppose I keep reading about it, writing about it, because it was interesting and because I've all done so much research on it.

07:45.420 --> 07:48.180
But it's a shame not to use the material.

07:49.900 --> 07:53.340
Kelo's slang term for a police person in the Doppelganger gambit is Leo.

07:53.780 --> 07:55.920
We asked her to explain the origin of this expression.

07:57.280 --> 08:04.680
I think I was seeing something about law enforcement officers one time, and I noticed that it made Leo.

08:05.160 --> 08:12.180
And I thought, that's great, because it gave rise in my mind to all kinds of connotations.

08:12.180 --> 08:21.300
And I could see police officers enjoying being called Leo because of the lion, the fierce kind of association you get with it.

08:21.440 --> 08:29.680
And therefore calling police stations lion, then, and someone who's likely to be picked up by the police is lion meat.

08:31.340 --> 08:37.080
The memorable lead characters in the Doppelganger gambit, both Leo's, are partnered throughout the book.

08:37.080 --> 08:42.360
They manage to transcend all sexual and philosophical barriers ultimately to solve the case.

08:42.800 --> 08:47.340
Listen as Kelo explains how she came up with the characters of Jana Brill and Mama Maxwell.

09:07.080 --> 09:14.300
For contrast, I gave her a male partner, and I can't remember why I decided to make him black.

09:16.660 --> 09:26.360
One of these things that just kind of happened, somebody later pointed out that I had my female character was the one that was working by the book and procedure,

09:26.600 --> 09:34.040
and my male character was the one who was working on intuition, which is an interesting reverse on the way people generally think of males and females.

09:34.720 --> 09:41.880
And that just sort of happened. The characters sort of balanced one another, but a lot of the balance was unconscious on my part.

09:44.440 --> 09:49.140
Jana Brill and Mama Maxwell are a fascinating pair. We asked Kelo if she plans to use them again.

09:50.340 --> 09:52.900
They were fun characters, and I intend to work with them again.

09:53.700 --> 10:00.700
Kelo wrote another police procedure novel, set in the same future history. This book is called Deadly Silence with a T.

10:00.700 --> 10:05.640
In this novel, Taryn Leos are transported to the planet Egar to function as peace officers.

10:06.460 --> 10:12.780
There they must operate under different rules. Their first duty is to aid the victims of crimes, rather than to pursue the perpetrator.

10:13.500 --> 10:14.800
How did Kelo come up with this role?

10:14.800 --> 10:31.920
I suppose it reflects a little bit of a reaction to some of the things that I've seen in our own culture, where the victim suffers a lot because everybody's so interested in catching the guy who did it.

10:32.140 --> 10:35.760
A lot of times they're not paying too much attention to the victim himself.

10:36.480 --> 10:41.600
In another twist, the Leos must function as defense attorneys when the perpetrator is brought to trial.

10:42.320 --> 10:44.340
Tomorrow, more on Arthur Lee Kelo.

