12:30.460 --> 12:35.320
Another novel by Kelo goes by the unlikely title, the Monitor, the Miners, and the Shree.

12:35.900 --> 12:42.000
It differs from the works we discussed previously in that it is said in another future history, one called the Sodality.

12:42.580 --> 12:46.080
Listen as Kelo talks about the origins and the inhabitants of this universe.

12:54.200 --> 12:57.900
It's very peaceful and wonderful and tended to get much more complex and much more violent.

12:58.160 --> 13:02.360
The older I got, the more I realized that people just didn't get along with each other all the time.

13:03.320 --> 13:09.240
I had several short stories that are set in that particular universe, and I'll probably come back to it again.

13:09.520 --> 13:17.760
It's an interesting one because it has a lot of different groups, none of which are human, and offers possibilities for societies and interplays.

13:19.560 --> 13:27.240
An alien, in the future history I have set up the one that most of the novels are in, has a minimal of aliens,

13:27.480 --> 13:31.800
so far we've actually gone on to run across one, which is spacing.

13:33.620 --> 13:45.060
And then of course there's aliens that are on the planet on which the colonists who are in trouble on the invictus land of the book I'm working on

13:45.060 --> 13:46.480
and that's not the moment that has some aliens on it.

13:46.620 --> 13:54.140
But there's a minimal of aliens, and if I want to deal with alien species it's just really easy to go to that other future history,

13:54.260 --> 13:56.880
which has all kinds of aliens running around.

13:58.180 --> 14:03.420
I like to think that it's just being across, being on our same galaxy, it's just on the other side,

14:03.500 --> 14:07.480
way out of contact with us, probably not where we're likely to run into it very soon.

14:09.540 --> 14:15.400
The plot of the Monitor of the Miners in the Shrie is centered about the fact that representatives of the Department of Surveys and Charters

14:15.400 --> 14:21.960
are sent to monitor the world naira, a proscripted world, for any signs of progress among the primitive inhabitants, the Shrie.

14:22.660 --> 14:31.400
The team discovers that a corporation by the name of Imra has been actively mining the planet for 500 years, an action strictly forbidden by the sodality.

14:32.200 --> 14:34.520
The last chapter of the novel is a courtroom scene.

14:35.100 --> 14:39.960
We asked Killow for husband Pat, who happens to be a lawyer, offered her any advice on its content.

14:41.160 --> 14:46.980
In fact, the lawyer half wrote that particular chapter, he was telling me, oh, this character ought to say that,

14:47.240 --> 14:51.020
and then you ought to bring up this point, and then you ought to counter with that legal point.

14:51.640 --> 14:58.440
And the whole chapter definitely got submitted to him for scrutiny as a procedure in logical thinking.

14:58.440 --> 15:04.300
So he's happy at, he's half the creator of that last chapter.

15:06.740 --> 15:10.500
Recently, a book of Killow's short stories appeared under the name Aventine.

15:11.020 --> 15:17.340
This is a collection of loosely connected stories, all set in the city of Aventine, a cultural and fine arts center.

15:18.020 --> 15:22.420
The stories are told from a first person point of view. We asked Killow why she chose this approach.

15:22.420 --> 15:31.860
I like those particular stories from a first person point of view because you can understand then,

15:33.380 --> 15:37.360
the storyteller is always victimized in some way in those particular stories.

15:38.740 --> 15:45.900
And you see inside of him, and you don't see things outside, you just see things entirely from his point of view,

15:45.900 --> 15:48.500
and why you may think he's dumb and getting trapped like that.

15:49.060 --> 15:53.220
Why, you can see why he ends up being victimized.

15:55.100 --> 16:01.460
Besides writing, singing, drawing, dancing, and theater are artistic influences in Killow's background.

16:02.160 --> 16:05.740
It was this experience that helped inspire her to write the Aventine stories.

16:06.360 --> 16:08.120
We asked her how the ideas developed.

16:09.640 --> 16:16.620
Most of those stories came out of images. There'd be like one single image.

16:21.060 --> 16:27.280
I liked the image of a pair of footprints scarlet in sand going away.

16:27.380 --> 16:31.860
The image just kept with me and kept with me until I found a story to go with it.

16:33.140 --> 16:37.680
Lee Killow is a dedicated, conscientious writer from whom we can expect more fine work.

